Philanthropist and African Entrepreneur, Tony Elumelu dressed up as pop icon Micheal Jackson in the 70s' Disco-themed Christmas party of one of his companies, the Heir Holdings. Elumelu who is worth over $1.4 billion looked dapper as he tried to mimic the late Icon whom he says he is a huge fan of. Elumelu has been named by Forbes as one of the 20 most powerful people in Africa. He has founded several companies including the Tony Elumelu Foundation, a non-profit organization that grants funds to budding entrepreneurs and is the chairman of UBA Group. Watch video here